<HEADLINE> Inter Milan Beats Sing Tao in HK Soccer International </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Italian soccer giants Inter
Milan trounced Hong Kong's first division side of Sing Tao 8-0 in
the China-HK Telelink Cup International Football Tournament here
Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
The tournament at the Hong Kong Stadium today was one of the
major sporting events before Hong Kong's handover at midnight on
June 30 this year.
</P>
<P>
In a dramatic move for the local sports fans, the 13-time
Italian league champions readily brought their sensational
full-strength line-up to Asia for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Among the big names on the team are Ivan Zamorano from Chile,
Aron Winter from the Netherlands, Paul Ince from England, Youri
Djorkaeff and Jocelyn Angloma from France, and Nicola Berti,
Salvatore Fresi and Gianluca Pagliuca from Italy.
</P>
<P>
Sing Tao has been very successful this season, with victories
in the Viceroy Cup, Regional Council Cup and F.A. President Cup
sevens. In the F.A. Cup, the other major Cup tournament of the
local sport, Sing Tao finished runners-up to Instant Dict.
</P>
<P>
Although the local side was reinforced today by such guest
players as Mark Wright, the former England captain and current
captain of Liverpool, and John Barnes, also from England, the
Italians were too much for the Sing Tao team.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan led the first half 3-0, with all the goals scored
by right winger Maurizio Ganz.
</P>
<P>
The Italians went on with their fast and well-coordinated
offensives in the second half. After a goal by Zamorano only three
minutes after the break, the Italians found the net four more
times in the last 20 minutes of the game.
</P>
<P>
Inter Milan will continue their Asian tour on Friday, when they
leave here for Bangkok, for Thailand's Premier Cup. 
</P>
</TEXT>
