<HEADLINE> UAE Sets Up Satellite Firm </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates has
formally set up its first satellite company with a fully paid up
capital of some 25 million dollars, sources in the company said
today.
</P>
<P>
The company, named Al Thurayya Space Communications Company,
was established on Monday under the terms of a ministerial decree
issued by Minister of Economy and Commerce Sheikh Fahim bin
Sultan al Qasimi, they said.
</P>
<P>
According to the decree, the company's capital will be divided
into 9.175 million shares with per value of around 2.6 dollars.
</P>
<P>
The largest single shareholder is Etisalat, the UAE's national
communications company which will hold around 3.2 million shares.
</P>
<P>
The company with a set life of 100 years variable by
resolution of its general assembly will be based in Abu Dhabi,
the UAE's capital, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The company would be charged with the responsibility of
handling the designing, developing, manufacturing, operating,
servicing and controlling of Etisalat satellites, they said.
</P>
</TEXT>
