<HEADLINE> Future Manufacturing Exhibition Unveiled in London </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A shop window on the future of
manufacturing in Europe was unveiled today at London's Science
Museum.
</P>
<P>
The Manufacturing for the Future exhibition marks the climax of
the UK chairmanship of EUREKA, the pan-European network of
market-oriented, collaborative R&AMP;D between companies, research
organizations and higher education institutes.
</P>
<P>
EUREAK's main aim is to enhance the competitiveness and
productivity of European companies. The exhibition features many
projects sponsored by EUREKA.
</P>
<P>
EUREAK has played an important part in the last 12 years in
encouraging European industry to innovate and develop new products
and processes through collaboration.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the exhibition, John Battle, minister of science,
said, "Wealth is created from excellence in science and technology
generation. Innovation, of which R&AMP;D plays an important part, is
all about the successful exploitation of new ideas."
</P>
<P>
He expressed the hope that the exhibition will act as a
stimulus to attract the young scientists and engineers of tomorrow
into the exciting world of innovation and engineering.
</P>
<P>
Launched in 1985, EUREKA has now 25 member countries. The
Manufacturing for the Future exhibition will run from June 18 to
October 28. 
</P>
</TEXT>
