<HEADLINE> Turkish Prime Minister Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Pro-Islamic Turkish Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan announced here today that he resigned, and would
hand over power to his junior partner center-right True Path Party
(DYP) leader Tansu Ciller.
