<HEADLINE> Hk to Be Real Democratic after Handover: Mahathir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohammed said here Wednesday that real democracy and freedom will
be obtained in Hong Kong only after the Chinese government resumes
the exercise of sovereignty over it.
</P>
<P>
Answering a question from a Xinhua journalist at a news
conference this afternoon, Mahathir pointed out that during more
than 100 years of Britain's colonial rule, "the British have never
given Hong Kong any freedom at all" and only after the handover
Hong Kong will become free and democratic.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on Hong Kong's return to China on July 1, the prime
minister said that for a long time the British exercised colonial
rule there and have never given Hong Kong any freedom at
all. "There was no elections that could suggest free will," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"Very soon Hong Kong will be under the sovereignty of
China. Only at that time it will certainly become democratic,"
Mahathir added.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader believed that Hong Kong will be a "real
democracy" because only "100 days ago it was given to Hong Kong a
free choice to decide who should be its chief executive (after
July 1)."
</P>
<P>
Mahathir left here Wednesday afternoon, widing up the first
official visit to Lebanon by a Malaysian head of government.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
