<HEADLINE> Israeli Embassy Denies Participation in Turkish </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Israeli embassy stressed here
today that there is no Israeli participation in the Turkish
military exercises, nor Israel has violated the sovereignty of
Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
A written statement released here by the Embassy of Israel
said "there is no Israeli participation whatsoever in the
Turkish exercises, which, as reported by the media, are
currently being held in the Eastern Mediterranean."
</P>
<P>
The statement was issued following the Cypriot government's
protest against the fresh violations of its territorial waters
and airspace by Turkish navy vessels and military aircraft.
</P>
<P>
Cyprus Defense Ministry confirmed here Tuesday that nine
Turkish navy vessels, namely two frigates, two destroyers, two
missile boats and three submarines, docked Monday in the ports
of Turkish-controlled Kyrenia, on the island's northern coast, and
Famagusta, on the eastern coast.
</P>
<P>
The vessels were taking part in the Turkish seaborne
military exercise "Sea Wolf '97".
</P>
<P>
The press reports have also said another five Turkish navy
vessels taking part in the same exercise sailed on Monday to
Haifa, Israel, where they will stay for four days.
</P>
<P>
But the Cyprus government did not mention whether Israel
has violated its sovereignty.
</P>
<P>
The Israeli Embassy statement reiterated that "Israel is not
violating the Flight Information Region (FIR) of Nicosia,
neither the territorial waters, nor the sovereignty of Cyprus."
</P>
