<DOCNO> XIE19970619.0036 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Calmness Returns After Feirce Fighting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, June 18 (Xinhua)-- Calmness has returned in the
Southern port town of Kismaio today after experiencing three
consecutive days of fierce fighting between the opposing
militiamen of Marehan and Majerten clans over the control of the
strategic port town.
</P>
<P>
Businessmen have reopened their commercial centers inside the
town and civilian vehicles were once again seen in the streets as
the fighting seemed to have spontaneously stopped and no bullets
were being beard in the hostile city.
</P>
<P>
Nevertheless, the rival militiamen of both clans have remained
in their defensive positions outside Kismaio. The reason for the
abrupt halt of the fighting is not yet disclosed as there has
been no peace initiatives made by any of the warring sides.
</P>
<P>
At least 30 people have died and as many as 65 others were
wounded since the armed clashes began between the two Darod
subclans in Kismaio four days ago. The Majerten fighters loyal to
General Mohamed Said Hirsi Morgan are now in full control of the
town while the Marehan clansmen still remain at Luglow village
about 15 KM North of the city.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, five people were killed and six others were wounded
when armed militiamen have indiscriminately fired upon two
transport lorries near Alolwein village, about 70 Km North of
Mogadishu early this morning. According to eyewitnesses on the
ground, the militiamen have been manning an illegal checkpoint
where they have been extorting money from the lorries.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitnesses said the lorry drivers have tried to defy the
orders of the militiamen as the armed men have immediately
changed their mind from asking for extortion money to a total
looting on the vehicles. As a result all passengers on board the
lorries were forced to get down and were looted to their heels
except 11 of them who are still missing. The lorries left Haji
Ali village on their way to Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The wounded were later evacuated to the ICRC run Keysaney
hospital of North Mogadishu for treatment. North Mogadishu
authorities have sent a security militia servicemen from the
Islamic courts headquarters to the sandy road along the coast to
find the culprits and clear the road from the illegal roadblocks.
</P>
<P>
In another development, five people were killed in Jilib town
of Middle Jubba region when two rival clan militiamen fought in
the town yesterday. According to the report the fighting has
sparked off after militiamen from Sheikhal clans have hijacked a
Suleman clan owned vehicle. The fighting has subsided when elders
from the two clans have intervened in the situation to contain
the hostility, however the fate of the looted vehicle is not yet
known. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
