<HEADLINE> Angola to Sign SADC Mining Cooperation Agreement </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Angolan Minister of Geology and
Mines Marcos Samondo said here today that his country will ink
the protocol on mines cooperation and integration of the Southern
African Development Community (SADC).
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks at a news conference before he is leaving
on Thursday for Swaziland to attend a conference on mines of the
Southern African Development Community to be held from June 25 to
27.
</P>
<P>
The minister said the above-mentioned document is very
important and will push all SADC member states to make their
joint efforts to realize the integration of mines sectors in
southern Africa by coordinating their mining policies.
</P>
<P>
The signature of the protocol will help strengthen mining
cooperation between Angola and other SADC nations as well as
promote the rejuvenation of Angola's mining sector, said Samondo.
</P>
<P>
He added that his country, rich in mineral resources, will
take necessary measures to attract and protect foreign investment
for developing its mining sector. 
</P>
