<HEADLINE> Mahathir Raps U.S. Congress for Resolution (I) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir
Mohammed said here today that the U.S. congress, which voted last
week to recognize Jerusalem as Israel's capital, "is not
contributing anything" to the Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a press conference before his departure this
afternoon, Mahathir said the U.S. congress "is totally insensitive
to what is happening here" in the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
On June 10, the U.S. House of Representatives voted
overwhelmingly the resolution recognizing Jerusalem as the
"undivided and permanent" capital of Israel, and set aside 100
million dollars to move the U.S. embassy to the city from
Tel Aviv.
</P>
<P>
Before winding up his three-day official visit in Lebanon,
Mahathir attacked the U.S. congressmen for only seeing "with a
blinked view of this region."
</P>
<P>
They only make the situation "more difficult because these
people are not sensitive and they don't understand the complexity
in this region," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysia premier reiterated his country's "full" support
for U.N. Security Council Resolution 425, which calls for an
unconditional Israeli withdrawal from south Lebanon, and urged
the world community to force Israel to comply with U.N.
resolutions.
</P>
<P>
"We think the world should provide pressure, and the big
powers should live up to their promise that they will help
to enforce whatever the resolutions passed by the United
Nations," Mahathir said.
</P>
</TEXT>
