<HEADLINE> Ethiopia's Petroleum Price to Remain Unchanged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Ethiopian petroleum
enterprise today said there will not be any increase in the price
of petroleum and derivatives as a result of the recent decision
by Ethiopia to import refined petroleum.
</P>
<P>
According to an earlier announcement by the enterprise, the
Assab oil refinery of Eritrea will stop operating as on August 1,
this year because the imported refined petroleum is cheaper than
using the refinery.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise said today that all the necessary arrangements
have been made to ensure the reliable flow of petroleum into the
market and there will not be any shortage due to the shift.
</P>
<P>
The enterprise further assured the public that they would even
get better service under the new scheme and any fear of
disruption of flow and shortage is unjustifiable.
</P>
<P>
Ethiopia needs about 830,000 metric tonnes of kerosene and
benzine and 4,700 metric tonnes of liquefied petroleum gas
annually. 
</P>
</TEXT>
