<HEADLINE> British NGO Clears 3,000 Landmines in Central </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A British non-governmental
organization "The Halo Trust" has removed 3,000 landmines and
more than 30,000 explosives of other kinds in Angola's central
Bie Province.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed yesterday by the NGO's spokesman Paul Heslop
in Kuito, capital city of Bie Province.
</P>
<P>
He said among Angola's 18 provinces, Bie has the biggest
number of landmines underground. It is estimated that more than
one million landmines had been planted in the province during its
prolonged anti-colonial war and civil war.
</P>
<P>
Heslop said that 150 mine fields had been discovered in Bie
Province, among which 22 have been cleared, adding that his
organization is busy removing mines in five heavy mine fields.
</P>
