<HEADLINE> Cypriot House Delegation Visits Russia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- A Cypriot delegation of the
House of Representatives left here today for Moscow for an
official visit aimed at seeking support from Russia on Cyprus
problem.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to reporters before their departure, House President
Spyros Kyprianou, who heads the delegation, said "this visit
underlines the great importance we attach to the growth of
relations between the two parliaments and also to the
strengthening of the ties of friendship and cooperation between
the two governments as well as the peoples of Russia and
Cyprus in all fields."
</P>
<P>
He noted that given current conditions surrounding the Cyprus
problem and what may arise in the near future, the House
attaches great importance to the visit "because we believe the
Russian element will be very useful to the Cyprus issue".
</P>
<P>
The five parliamentary party leaders, who make up of the
delegation, also issued statements today expressing their common
view that Turkish troops should be withdrawn from the island
once a solution to the protracted Cyprus problem is reached.
</P>
<P>
The visit took place less than a month ahead the
U.N.-sponsored direct talks between leaders of the two Cypriot
communities, scheduled to begin on July 9, near New York.
</P>
<P>
Russia has expressed its firm support for a solution to
the Cyprus problem and pledged to help the current U.N.
initiative on Cyprus.
</P>
<P>
During their stay, the delegation is expected to have
separate meetings with Russian Duma President Gennady Selezniov,
Federation Council Vice-President Vasili Likhachev, Foreign Ministry
officials and political party leaders. 
</P>
