<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tanzanian First Lady Stresses Reducing Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The first lady, Mama Anna
Mkapa said today that no effort to fight poverty can succeed if
it does not address the poverty that affiliated women and
children in developing countries.
</P>
<P>
Launching the 1997 Huma Development Report (HDR) at the
national level in Dar es Salaam, the first lady said women's
contribution to the poverty eradication initiatives was
neccessary.
</P>
<P>
She said at the Kilimanjaro Hotel here that since women
constitute more than 51 percent of the world's population, their
participation in the fight against poverty was of paramount
importance.
</P>
<P>
Globally, the report which was prepared by the UN Development
Program (UNDP) was launched simultaneously last Thursday in Bonn,
Germany and Cape Town in South Africa.
</P>
<P>
"There is now increased awareness of women issues in current
government thinking and policy formulation, but that is only the
beginning of a long process towards reducing poverty among women
and children," she said.
</P>
<P>
On the economic front, the first lady said affirmative action
towards eradicating poverty would be useless if the economy was not
growing.
</P>
<P>
"If the economy is not growing, or if our countries have to
spend more money on debt-servicing than on health and education,
the ones who suffer most are women and children," she said.
</P>
<P>
She said it was therefore, important for governments and
international aid organisations and the donor community to relate
the well-being of women and children to economic trends within
countries and internationally.
</P>
<P>
The first lady also said poverty could be fought if
governments jack up the informal sector.
</P>
<P>
On peace, she said, African countries, including Tanzania,
needed to get rid of causes of refugees if it wanted to eradicate
poverty.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the same function, the UNDP Resident
Representative and the UN Resident Co-ordinator, J. Victor Angelo
said good governance was crucial for poverty eradication
initiatives.
</P>
<P>
The launching ceremony was also attended by members of the
diplomatic corps, the donor community and government officials.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
