<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Financing for Panama's Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of a 28 million U.S. dollar loan to help finance
Panama's poverty alleviation project.
</P>
<P>
The Social Investment Fund Project will benefit the
disadvantaged communities and population groups from Panama's
poorest districts by addressing their demands for priority
infrastructure and services and provide support for productive
activities of micro-entreprenteurs.
</P>
<P>
The total project cost is estimated at some 80 million dollars.
In addition to the World Bank loan, the Inter-American Development
Bank will provide a 28 million dollar loan and the remaining 24
million dollars will come from the government of Panama and the
beneficiaries. 
</P>
