<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Plane Crash in Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Two people were killed today when a
private plane crashed in Western Turkey, the semi-official
Anatolia News Agency reported tonight.
</P>
<P>
The agency said that Cessna-172 type four-man private
aircraft crashed at Osmaniye village of Bozdogan town in Aydin
province, killing one person on the spot and another person
died after being taken to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
Investigations into the crash of the plane are underway,
said the agency. 
