<HEADLINE> UAE Calls For Solidarity with Palestinians </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The United Arab Emirates(UAE)
today called for Arab countries to work out a "concrete stand" to
support Palestinian people, local television reported.
</P>
<P>
Meeting with visiting Palestinian President Yasser Arafat,
UAE's Deputy Prime Minister Sheikh Sultan bin Zayed al Nahyan
stressed the Arab world should continue support to the
Palestinians until they could enjoy their legal rights.
</P>
<P>
Such a stand demands supports from all Arabs and the
international community to bring the stalled Middle East peace
process back on track, the UAE official said.
</P>
<P>
He also praised Palestinians' struggle against Israel, saying
his country will continue to support Palestinians in the peace
process.
</P>
<P>
He also criticized the U.S. House of Representatives resolution
Tuesday declaring Jerusalem as Israel's undivided capital.
</P>
<P>
The resolution will harm the peace process and will
exacerbating the situation in the Middle East region, he said,
warning "it is likely to lead (the peace process) to a collapse."
</P>
<P>
On his part, Arafat briefed the UAE deputy prime minister on
the latest developments in the Middle East peace process and
pointed to major difficulties in realizing a just and
comprehensive peace.
</P>
<P>
The difficulties were caused by Israeli government's hardline
policies, particularly the occupation of Arab lands, the
construction of settlements and efforts to turn Jerusalem a
Israeli Jerusalem, Arafat said.
</P>
<P>
Arafat arrived here this afternoon on an official visit to the
Emirates, the second leg of his multi-nation Gulf tour to seek
support for the Palestinians in the peace process.
</P>
<P>
The tour, which had taken him to Saudi Arabia, began as
violence resumed in the occupied Arab lands and Israeli troops
shot and wounded dozens of Palestinians in the West Bank city of
Hebron. 
</P>
