<HEADLINE> Number of Tourists on Increase in Zanzibar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The number of tourists
coming to Zanzibar rose to 95,464 during 1996/97 financial year
from 56,415 in the previous year, a report reaching here said
today.
</P>
<P>
Minister for Information, Tourism, Culture and Youth, Issa
Mohammed told the House of Representatives in the town of
Zanzibar when answering a question concerned that the government
earned 1.1 billion Tanzania Shillings (about 1.83 million US
Dollars) from various taxes charged on the tourists and hotels.
</P>
<P>
He said the earlier projections during the period, which stood
at about 70,000 visitors, had been surpassed by 25,000 tourists
more.
</P>
<P>
The minister attributed the influx of tourists to vigorous
campaign by the government and people to publicize Zanzibar as a
tourist paradise.
</P>
<P>
About 45 percent of Zanzibar's gross domestic product (GDP)
was generated by the tourism sector last fiscal year. 
</P>
