<HEADLINE> US Software Giant to Set Up Research Lab in UK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Microsoft Corporation, one of
the software giants in the United States, has announced that it
would spend 80 million US dollars to set up a research laboratory
in Cambridge, England, in collaboration with Cambridge University,
the New York Times reported today.
</P>
<P>
The move is considered a "significant step" Microsoft took in
the direction to build a world-class research team.
</P>
<P>
The Cambridge venture is Micrfosoft's first overseas research
lab. The move is prompted by the comapny's realization that even
the millionaire-making prospect of Microsoft shares have not been
sufficient in luring leading computer scientists. "Going to Europe
gives us a way to hire people who bring new talents and new
perspectives to our work that we couldn't get any other way,"
Nathan Myhrvold, Microsoft's chief technology officer, was quoted
as saying.
</P>
<P>
The research community views Microsoft's venture as another
sign that the software giant is exceptional in an era of deficit
reduction and corporate belt-tightening--a time when the Federal
Government and most companies are curbing their spending on basic
research. 
</P>
</TEXT>
