<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Leaves for G-8 Summit in Denver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin
left here today for the U.S. city of Denver, Colorado, to attend a
summit of a new Group of Eight (G-8) as an equal partner alongside
leaders of other seven industrialized nations.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Russia to attend the summit of the
Group Seven (G-7), comprising the United States, Britain, France,
Germany, Canada, Italy and Japan. Russia's participation as a
full member transforms the G-7 into a G-8.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin will be invited to open the summit, which is scheduled
for June 21-22, and to participate in the discussion of global,
regional, political, economic, social and financial issues, said
Russian presidential spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky.
</P>
<P>
During the summit, Russia will also put forth some proposals
concerning global energy problems and cooperation in environmental
protection and seismic forecasting.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that the summit participants will also discuss
terrorism, including computer terrorism, and nuclear
non-proliferation.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin is expected to fly back to Moscow on June 23. 
</P>
</TEXT>
