<HEADLINE> Saudi Arabia's Al-Hilal Wins Asian Super Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia's Al-Hilal lifted the
Asian Soccer Super Cup title on Thursday after drawing 1-1 with
Pohang Steelers of South Korea in the second leg in Pohang for a
2-1 aggregate victory.
</P>
<P>
The Asian club champion Steelers took the lead in the 13th
minute when Seo Hyo-won pounced on a loose ball and scored with a
swerving shot from 25 meters.
</P>
