<HEADLINE> Hk Convention Center Almost Ready for Ceremonies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- With the day of Hong Kong's
return to China near at hand, the Hong Kong Convention and
Exhibition Center, the venue for the handover ceremony, has become
the attraction of the world.
</P>
<P>
Workers are working day and night at the seabird-shaped
extension of the existing HKCEC. Each day is bringing new changes
to the fifth-floor grand hall where the handover ceremony is
scheduled to be held and to its seventh-floor main hall where the
ceremony for the establishment of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region and the swearing-in will be held. Internal
decoration for the extension has been completed, and work has
started to install lights and other equipment.
</P>
<P>
Flagpoles are being erected on the podium of the fifth-floor
handover ceremony hall.
</P>
<P>
The extension of HKCEC costing 4.8 billion Hong Kong dollars to
build is located on a 6.5-hectare island site reclaimed from the
Wan Chai waterfront.
</P>
<P>
The combined HKCEC boasts five exhibition halls, two convention
halls and 52 conference rooms. It is Asia's second largest
exhibition and convention complex, only after the Tokyo
International Exhibition Center, and is capable of accommodating
up to 140,000 visitors a day. 
</P>
</TEXT>
