<HEADLINE> Stamps to Be Issued to Mark HK Return to Motherland </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese Ministry of Post and
Telecommunications will issue a set of four stamps on July 1 to
commemorate Hong Kong's return to the motherland.
</P>
<P>
A pair out of the four stamps are commemorative ones, namely
"Hong Kong's Return to the Motherland." They are designed with the
Chinese characters for "Sino-British Joint Declaration on the
Question of Hong Kong," and the "Basic Law of the Hong Kong
Special Administrative Region of the People's Republic of China."
</P>
<P>
The other two are souvenir sheets with the same design, but one
of them coated with gold. A portrait of Deng Xiaoping and the
Chinese characters for "one country, two systems" are printed
against a background of Hong Kong scenery on the sheetlet.
</P>
<P>
The gold-coated sheetlet will be the first
of its kind ever issued in China since it was founded in 1949.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Post and Telecommunications in 1995 issued a
set of four stamps featuring scenic spots in Hong Kong, and in
1996 another set of four stamps related to Hong Kong's economic
construction. 
</P>
</TEXT>
