<HEADLINE> HK Return Boosts Macao People's Confidence in Future: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A senior Chinese official said here
today that Hong Kong's return to the motherland will help boost
Macao people's confidence in future.
</P>
<P>
Wang Qiren, director of the Xinhua News Agency Macao Branch,
told about 20 representatives of Macao youth organizations, which
last month formed a preparatory committee for the celebration of
Hong Kong's handover, that Hong Kong's return is "inspiring and
serves as a model" for Macao.
</P>
<P>
"The concept of 'one country, two systems' will become reality
in Hong Kong in 12 days," he noted, after listening to briefings
by members of the committee here. "People around the world are
convinced that Hong Kong will remain prosperous under that
policy."
</P>
<P>
"The success of Hong Kong in implementing the policy will help
boost the confidence of Macao residents in carrying out the policy
in Macao in 1999 after China resumes its exercise of sovereignty
over Macao," he added.
</P>
<P>
Kou Hoi In, executive chairman of the preparatory committee,
briefed Wang on the preparations for celebrations, which, among
others, include a symposium and a gala.
</P>
<P>
"The establishment of the preparatory committee is aimed at
enabling all Macao youths to share the happiness of Hong Kong's
return (to the motherland)," Kou said. "It also helps us get
united and do our best for a smooth return of Macao."  
</P>
</TEXT>
