<HEADLINE> Morbidelli Breaks Arm in Car Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Formula One driver Gianni Morbidelli
was taken to hospital with a broken left arm after a high-speed
crash during testing at the French circuit of Magny-Cours on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The Sauber driver lost control of his car at the Imola chicane
and is reported to have destroyed the chassis in the impact.
</P>
<P>
Morbidelli, who was taken to a hospital in nearby Nevers, will
definitely miss the French Grand Prix on June 29 and is likely to
be out of action for at least six weeks. 
