<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: "One Country, Two Systems" Policy Practical </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's smooth return to China
on July 1 proves that Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two
systems" was practical, two Macao celebrities have said.
</P>
<P>
Both Edmundo Ho Hau-Wah, president of the Macao Bankers'
Association and member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth
National People Congress, and Ng Fok, a well-known businessman and
member of the Standing Committee of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made
these remarks in a recent exclusive interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return, as a major event in the history of Chinese
nation, is an important beginning in the course of China's
peaceful reunification," Ho said. "A pioneering undertaking, the
concept of 'one country, two systems' will help promote the
peaceful reunification with Taiwan as well."
</P>
<P>
He said that Macao can learn from Hong Kong's experience in
the implementation of the policy, although Macao is different from
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's success is very important to Macao as Macao will
also return to the motherland in 1999 when the policy of 'one
country, two systems' will be implemented," he said. "Macao's
transition will enter into a new stage after Hong Kong's return."
</P>
<P>
He urged people in Macao to support Hong Kong for the success
of the policy, saying it is vital not only to Hong Kong and Macao,
but also to the Chinese nation as a whole.
</P>
<P>
When a nation resumes its exercise of sovereignty over a piece
of land occupied by other nations, Ho noted, there are always war
and blood. But the policy of "one country, two systems" has for
the first time in the world history resolved that issue in a
peaceful way.
</P>
<P>
"Although there were ups and downs during the past 13 years,
Hong Kong remains basically prosperous and stable if viewing the
whole transition process," he said. "That should first be
attributed to the concept of 'one country, two systems.'"
</P>
<P>
In addition, the financier said that Hong Kong's successful
transition should also be a result of China's political stability
and economic growth.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ng Fok, a leading entrepreneur in the territory,
said Hong Kong's return marks the coming of a new historic epoch,
as Hong Kong will be governed by Hong Kong people and China makes
the first step in the peaceful reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's success proves that Deng Xiaoping's concept
of 'one country, two systems' is a feasible way in the peaceful
reunification of the motherland," he said. "It is also a good idea
in handling disputes left over from history between different
nations."
</P>
<P>
The entrepreneur urged other businessmen to invest in Macao
and help contribute to a successful transition.
</P>
<P>
"We should take the return of Hong Kong as an encouragement,"
he said. "We should help cultivate a stable transition in Macao
through more investment to promote local economy." 
</P>
</TEXT>
