<HEADLINE> Xiamen-Taiwan Trade Promotion Center Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A Xiamen-Taiwan trade promotion
center, the first of its kind in China, was set up today in the
coastal city of Xiamen, a special economic zone in southeast China.
</P>
<P>
The center is aimed at carrying out the central government's
policies toward Taiwan, enhancing economic and trading exchanges
across the two sides of the Taiwan Straits, and organizing the
annual Xiamen-Taiwan export commodity fair.
</P>
<P>
In addition, it will hold professional training courses in
economic and trading fields for both sides, conduct studies on
trade with Taiwan, and help businesses in the inland areas to
expand trade with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Over the past dozen years, Xiamen has become one of the inland
area's major ports to trade with Taiwan, and is the area which has
the most investment by Taiwanese businessmen.
</P>
<P>
A city official said in early April that Xiamen had approved
nearly 1,400 Taiwanese-funded projects which involved a
contractual investment of about 2.9 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
With the city's geographical advantage, nearly 1.3 billion US
dollars worth of goods were exported to Taiwan via Xiamen in
1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
