<HEADLINE> Wimbledon Organizers to Increase Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Security at the Wimbledon Tennis
Championships to start here Monday will be tightened up, the
organizing All-England Club said on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The club said two car parks would be moved to create a
"sterile" area of around 200 meters along one of the main roads.
</P>
<P>
All bags will be examined when spectators enter the grounds and
all vehicles will be checked in addition to the usage of closed
circuit television cameras which record the traffic in the
concourse.
</P>
<P>
Organizers hope that the championships, which are expected to
attract around 400,000 visitors over the two weeks, would not
repeat what happened in April's Grand National steeplechase.
</P>
<P>
A bomb scare caused the race to be postponed for two days.
</P>
