<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua Inspects Natural Gas Pipeline Project </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Vice-Premier Zou Jiahua inspected
a construction site of the Shaanxi-Beijing natural gas pipeline
project today, calling on workers to do their utmost to ensure the
quality and quick completion of the pipeline.
</P>
<P>
The 840-km line is designed to pipe natural gas from northwest
China's Shaanxi Province to Beijing. The project was started early
last year and will be completed by the end of this month.
</P>
<P>
By the end of September, Beijing residents will have access to
natural gas from the pipeline. And the capital city's air quality
is expected to be improved to a great extent as a result of the
line.
</P>
<P>
The vice-premier made detailed inquires about the project's
progress, quality management, design plans and gas prices, saying
he was pleased that the pipeline is of such outstanding quality.
</P>
<P>
Zou extended his regards to the construction workers and
praised them for their industrious spirit, calling on construction
units to make every effort to guarantee the quality, speed and
efficiency of the project.  
</P>
