<HEADLINE> Chiluba Calls for Africa's Economic Independence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick
Chiluba stressed here today that political independence in Africa
will never become a reality if African countries continue to be
economically dependent.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba made the remarks while he received the credentials from
the newly-appointed Philippine ambassador to Zambia.
</P>
<P>
The president urged the African governments to stand on their own
in the development of the continent if they are to manage their
independence.
</P>
<P>
Also earlier today while receiving the credentials from the new
Ethiopian ambassador to Zambia, President Chiluba urged countries
that have launched political and economic reforms to allow the
ordinary citizens to participate in the implementation of those
programs in their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
He noted that people should be allowed to play a part in the
running of their economies if the reforms are to succeed.
