<HEADLINE> New Cannons to be Fired after July 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- A new type of ceremonial cannon
will be put into use after July 1 as part of formal welcoming
activities to greet state and government leaders of foreign
countries to visit China, according to sources with China's armed
police.
</P>
<P>
The "86"-style cannons have been used for ceremonial purposes
by troops of the armed police forces for ten years. The new "97"
version is more sleekly designed and has a rich thundering sound
which can be heard from far away.
</P>
<P>
In March, 1984, China resumed the firing of cannons during
welcoming events for foreign VIPs. Up to now, the cannons have
been used 383 times in Tiananmen Square to greet foreign state
and government leaders. 
