the United States on the revision of the Japanese-US defense
cooperation guidelines.
</P>
<P>
Fu briefed Masahiro and his party on China's basic position and
views with regard to Japanese-US security cooperation. He pointed
out that the Japan-US security alliance was a bilateral
arrangement formed during Cold War times.
</P>
<P>
with the collapse of Cold War structure and under a relatively
stable situation in the Asia-Pacific region, He went on to say,
Japan and the US should adopt a prudent attitude toward their
cooperation in the military realm, and their military cooperation
should stay within the bilateral framework, so that no
complications will be added to the regional security situation.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that Japan will learn from its history in a
realistic and sincere way, and stay on the path of peaceful
development.
</P>
<P>
Xiong Guangkai, deputy chief of the PLA General Staff, attended
the meeting.  
</P>
