<HEADLINE> Major State-Owned Coal Mines to Lay Off 3,200 Workers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Major state-owned coal mines of
north China's Shanxi Province will lay off 3,200 employees this
year, in a bid to improve efficiency.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, the number of coal production
workers will be brought within 152,000 in these coal mines, and
the efficiency rate between crude coal produced and labor will be
3.37 tons per worker.
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, these coal mines will also distribute profits
to realize a simultaneous growth of enterprise gain and workers'
income.
</P>
<P>
The annual average income of the workers of the province's
major coal mines will reach 10,000 yuan this year. It is expected
that by the end of this year, average income of workers in the
province's coal mines will go up by 1,000 yuan from that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
Shanxi, dubbed as "sea of coal", is China's largest coal
producer. 
