<DOCNO> XIE19970619.0129 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interview: "One Country, Two Systems" Practicable </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's smooth return to China
on July 1 proves that Deng Xiaoping's concept of "one country, two
systems" is practicable, two Macao celebrities said.
</P>
<P>
Edmundo Ho Hau-Wah, president of the Macao Bankers' Association
and a member of the Standing Committee of the Eighth National
People's Congress, and Ng Fok, a well-known businessman and a
member of the National Committee of the Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC), made these remarks in a recent
exclusive interview with Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's return, as a major event in the history of the
Chinese nation, marks an important beginning in the course of
China's peaceful reunification," Ho said. "A pioneering
undertaking, the concept of 'one country, two systems' will help
promote the peaceful reunification with Taiwan as well."
</P>
<P>
He said Macao can learn from Hong Kong's experience in the
implementation of the policy, although Macao is different from
Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's success is very important to Macao as Macao will
also return to China in 1999 when the policy of 'one country, two
systems' will be implemented," he said. "Macao's transition will
enter into a new stage after Hong Kong's return."
</P>
<P>
He urged Macao people to support Hong Kong in ensuring the
success of the policy, saying it is vital not only to Hong Kong
and Macao, but also to the Chinese nation as a whole.
</P>
<P>
When a nation recovers a piece of land occupied by other
nations, Ho noted, there are always war and blood. But the policy
of "one country, two systems" has for the first time in the world
history resolved the issue in a peaceful way.
</P>
<P>
"Although there were ups and downs during the past 13 years,
Hong Kong remains basically prosperous and stable if viewing the
whole transition process," he said. "That should first be
attributed to the concept of 'one country, two systems.'"
</P>
<P>
In addition, the financier said, China's political stability
and economic growth is also credited with Hong Kong's successful
transition.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Ng Fok, a leading entrepreneur in the territory,
said Hong Kong's return marks the advent of a new historic epoch,
as Hong Kong will be governed by Hong Kong people themselves and
China takes its first step in the cause of peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
"Hong Kong's success proves that Deng Xiaoping's concept of
'one country, two systems' is a practicable way in the peaceful
reunification of the motherland," he said. "It is also a good idea
in handling disputes left over from history between nations."
</P>
<P>
He urged other businessmen to invest in Macao and help
contribute to a successful transition.
</P>
<P>
"We should take the return of Hong Kong as an encouragement,"
he said. "We should help cultivate a smooth transition in Macao
through more investment to promote the local economy."  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
