<HEADLINE> Uruguay Enters Second Round of World Youth Soccer Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Uruguay have virtually booked
a place in the second round after defeating host Malaysia 3-1 in a
Group A match of the World Youth Cup Finals at the Shah Alam
Stadium near here today.
</P>
<P>
Uruguay defeated belgium 3-0 in its first group match and now
collected 6 points with two wins, topping the four-team group
standings.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia opened the scoring in the 10th minute through Nik
Fadly, but Zalayeta of Uruguay used his height to equalize with a
powerful header in the 24th minute.
</P>
<P>
In the 37th minute, Malaysia conceded an own goal when Haled
Masron tapped in Nicolas Olivera's grounder. In the 75th minute
of the match, Lopez Mora of Uruguay added another goal.
</P>
<P>
Despite the second defeat, Malaysia, who lost to Morocco 1-3 in
their first match, still have a slim chance of making the second
round, provided that they beat Belgium in the last match.
</P>
<P>
In the France-South Korea group B match at Kuching, France
scored twice in the first two minutes to wrap up a comfortable 4-2
victory over South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Captain Thierry Henry scored a first-minute goal and David
Trezequet made it 2-0 in the second.
</P>
<P>
Thierry added another goal in the 10th minute and Trezequet
also scored his second goal in the 52nd minute to give France a
commanding 4-0 lead.
</P>
<P>
The South Koreans fought back through goals by Park Jin-Sup in
the 54th and 69th minutes.
</P>
<P>
In a group C match at Alor Setar, Ghana came from behind to
hold China to a 1-1 draw.
</P>
<P>
China went into the lead when Li Jinyu scored the team's lone
goal two minutes before half-time.
</P>
<P>
But the Ghanaians, 2-1 victors over Ireland on Tuesday,
dominated the Chinese defence after the break and were rewarded
by Stephen Appiah's equaliser in the 74th minute.
</P>
<P>
Ghana have four points and China one in group C. Ireland take
on the United States later on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Eight of the 24 teams will bow out after the preliminary league
as the top two and four best third-pace finishers from the six
groups advance to the last 16. The final will be played on July 5.
</P>
</TEXT>
