<HEADLINE> Aircraft "Spirit of Hong Kong 97" Arrives in HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Tung Chee Hwa, first chief
executive of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, today
attended a welcome ceremony for the "Spirit of Hong Kong 97", a
specially painted Cathay Pacific Boeing 747-200 commemorating the
return of Hong Kong to China.
</P>
<P>
The short ceremony was also attended by Cathay Pacific Deputy
Chairman Patrick Tsai.
The aircraft was welcome with a lion dance.
</P>
<P>
The design on the aircraft fuselage is based on the airline's
"Heart of Asia" print advertisements, with brushstroke depictions
of prominent buildings on the Hong Kong Island skyline, and the
Chinese Character "Jia", meaning "home".
</P>
<P>
The design was chosen because it is the spirit of Hong Kong
that drives the extraordinary success of Cathay Pacific's home,
and Hong Kong's skyline represents the aspirations and
achievements of its people, Tsai said.
</P>
<P>
It took 27 days to complete the repainting of the aircraft at
the Taikoo Aircraft Engineering Company facility in Xiamen, east
China.
</P>
<P>
Cathay Pacific's B747-200s serve the airline's regional and
Middle East routes, so the "Spirit of Hong Kong 97" will be seen
in various cities in the Asia region. It is envisaged that the
design will remain on the aircraft for at least one year.
</P>
