<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The group of eight Muslim
developing countries, or D-8, would continue with its founding
objectives despite the resignation of Turkish Prime Minister
Necmettin Erbakan who mooted the idea to form the grouping,
Malaysia said today.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Abdullah Ahmad Badawi stressed that Erbakan's
resignation yesterday will not affect D-8, the brainchild of
Erbakan, as those involved are not Erbakan but eight countries --
Malaysia, Bangladesh, Indonesia, Pakistan, Iran, Egypt, Nigeria
and Turkey.
</P>
