<HEADLINE> Arafat Ends Visit to UAE </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 18 (Xinhua)-- Palestinian President Yasser
Arafat left here today after a two-day official visit as part of
his Gulf tour to seek support for the Palestinians in the Middle
East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The United Arab Emirates was the second leg of his trip which
has taken him to Saudi Arabia. He will visit other Gulf
countries.
</P>
<P>
During his visit, Arafat met with some UAE top officials,
including UAE President Sheikh Zayed bin Sultan al Nahyan and
discussed with them the stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
Some diplomats here noted that Arafat hoped the UAE
and other Gulf countries would use their influence in Washington
to stop the implementation of a U.S. House of Representatives
resolution on recognizing Jerusalem as Israel's undivided capital.
</P>
<P>
Gulf countries have criticized the U.S. resolution which was
passed last week and set aside 100 million U.S. dollars to move the
U.S. Embassy from Tel Aviv to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
The diplomats also said that during his tour in the region,
Arafat will request aid from Saudi Arabia, the UAE, Bahrain,
Qatar, Kuwait and Oman.
</P>
<P>
Arafat began his tour as Israeli troops shot and wounded
dozens of Palestinians in the West Bank town of Hebron. Four
consecutive days of violence between the Israelis and
Palestinians reflect a further crack in the stalled Middle East
peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Middle East peace talks were set in deadlock after Israel
began the construction of a new settlement in East
Jerusalem in March. 
</P>
</TEXT>
