<BODY>
<HEADLINE> hkhk-High-speed Direct Internet Backbone Connecting Hong Kong and Guangzhou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
Hong Kong, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The first high-speed direct
Internet backbone connection between Hong Kong and Guangzhou was
inaugurated today, it was learned here.
</P>
<P>
Also launched were two new data communications services that
employ Integrated Services Digital Network (ISDN) and Frame Relay
technology.
</P>
<P>
The projects launched by Hong Kong Telecom and the Guangdong
Posts and Telecommunications Administration are believed to
provide customers of the two places with more choices of
cost-effective, fast and reliable data network solutions, sources
of HK Telecom said.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong Telecom's Netplus is the first and only Internet
backbone provider in the Asian region to have 512 Kbps direct
connection to China's Internet backbone, ChinaNet. Apart from the
new high-speed backbone, there are already direct links to Beijing
and Shanghai at present.
</P>
<P>
The new link further reinforces the position Hong Kong Telecom
as the Internet hub in Asia and a gateway to other parts of China,
Hong Kong Telecom experts claimed.
</P>
<P>
With the direct link, which will be upgraded to full T1 (1.5
Mbps) by the end of this year, customers can conduct business with
their mainland counterparts over the Internet in a much faster,
more reliable and secure environment and to generate more Internet
based business opportunities.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, customers can also use the Internet roaming services
already available in Beijing, Shanghai, Xiamen, Guangzhou and
Tianjin.
</P>
<P>
The ISDN services enable customers to transmit voice, fax, video
images and computer data simultaneously to several destinations at
high speed from 64Kbps to 384Kbps. Besides Guangzhou, the service
is also available in Beijing and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Frame Relay service also allows for simultaneous
communications with multiple destinations via a single access
line. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
