<HEADLINE> Xinhua Commentary on China's Resumption of Exercise of Sovereignty Over HK (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, June 19 (Xinhua)--Xinhua News Agency today published a
commentary on the importance of China's resuming of the exercises
of its sovereignty over Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
The commentary says the giant clock in the countdown board is
ticking to the last second when China will resume its exercise of
sovereignty over Hong Kong and the 1.2 billion Chinese people will
fulfill their dream. It could be imagined that millions of Chinese
all over the world will also hail the great day's arrival.
</P>
<P>
People all over the world who advocate justice and oppose
aggression, who have suffered servitude, humiliation and misery
from imperialism and colonialism will celebrate any event that
represents a new development in establishing an international
relationship marked with peace, stability, justice and fairness.
</P>
<P>
Through negotiations with Britain and with the adoption of the
"one country, two systems" principle, China resolved the
historical problem, resulting from imperialism and colonialism,
that was acceptable to all parties. China's resumption of the
exercise of sovereignty over Hong Kong sets an example for solving
nation-to-nation conflicts through peaceful means.
</P>
<P>
"This is one of China's major contributions to world peace,
progress and development," said the commentary.
</P>
</TEXT>
