<HEADLINE> PKK Kills 6 Turkish Soldiers in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- One Turkish officer and five
soldiers were killed and five others wounded in armed attacks by
the rebels of the outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) in
southeastern Turkey late Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
The semi-official Anatolia News Agency reported today that a
group of PKK militants used rockets and other weapons in attack on
the soldiers, in Gorenoluk village in Eruh town of Siirt province.
</P>
<P>
The soldiers were on their way back from the cross-border
military operations against the PKK in northern Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The wounded soldiers were rushed to Siirt State Hospital, said
the agency.
</P>
<P>
About 50,000-strong Turkish government troops began the
cross-border military operation in May 14 to attack the PKK rebels
in northern Iraq. At least 2,500 PKK members have been killed in
the operation, military said.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a near 13-year-old separatist war
for an independent Kurdish state, which has claimed over 23,000
lives in eastern and southeastern Turkey. 
</P>
