<HEADLINE> Beijing's Telecommunications Ready for Relay Celebrations </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Telecommunication service in
Beijing is well-equipped and ready for the relay of the capital
city's celebrations of Hong Kong's return.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the Beijing Telecommunication Bureau said China
will use 13 communication satellites over Asia and Pacific region
to broadcast the celebration activities to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
So far 29 television stations and news agencies from about 20
countries and regions have applied for renting satellite cables to
relay the celebration activities. The applicants also include
Taiwan media.
</P>
<P>
To make a successful relay, additional equipment has been
shipped in from Shanghai, Guangzhou, and other parts of
China. Beijing's satellite transmission capacity has also been
expanded.
</P>
<P>
The city's long-distance telephone service has opened 480
additional direct dial routes between Beijing and Hong
Kong. Telecommunication facilities especially for overseas
journalists are also ready for use. 
</P>
