<HEADLINE> Egypt: Hong Kong to Prosper After Handover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Egyptian Deputy Prime Minister
Youssef Wali has said that the prosperity and stability of Hong
Kong is guaranteed after its return to China on July 1.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua Wednesday, Wali dismissed as
"absurd predictions" some Western media reports that Hong Kong's
future development will be enfeebled by the transfer of power.
</P>
<P>
"China's economic reform has achieved sound success. This will
guarantee continuous prosperity and stability of Hong Kong in the
future," said Wali, who doubles as Minister of Agriculture and
Land Reclamation.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that the flesh-and-blood ties between Hong Kong and
its motherland are inseparable despite the alternative political
and economic systems Hong Kong inherits from the
one-century-and-half British rule.
</P>
<P>
Instead, Hong Kong will continue to serve as a major bridge for
China to associate and communicate with the outside world, he
added.
</P>
<P>
"The return of Hong Kong, which is an important step toward
China's reunification, will give a strong boost to the
revitalization of the nation," Wali said.
</P>
<P>
He also conveyed his congratulations to the Chinese people on
being able to wipe out their humiliations as the colonial rule
ends in Hong Kong at midnight on June 30. 
</P>
</TEXT>
