<HEADLINE> Study of Basic Law Urged </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Chinese law expert, Wu Jianfan,
urges his countrymen to increase their awareness of the Basic Law
of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region.
</P>
<P>
Wu, at the Chinese Academy of Social Sciences, said that it is
incorrect to think that the Basic Law is only implemented in Hong
Kong and has nothing to do with the inland areas of China.
</P>
<P>
"Many aspects stipulated by the law are the concerns of the
whole nation and relate to every citizen," said the expert, who
lectured on the Basic Law to president Jiang Zemin and other
Chinese leaders early this year.
</P>
<P>
"Some stipulations, like the capitalist system, can only suit
the situation in Hong Kong," Wu said. "But as rules prescribed by
the law, they must be observed and respected by the nation as a
whole, so that the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong can be
guaranteed in a real sense."
</P>
<P>
Wu, lecturing at the academy, said that attention should be
paid to several issues to ensure the implementation of the Basic
Law, including correctly handling the relations between the
central government and the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region
and the preservation of the region's old laws. 
</P>
</TEXT>
