<HEADLINE> hkhk-Hong Kong-Guangdong Boundary of Administration signed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- a Memorandum of Understanding
(MOU) concerning the boundary of administration between Hong Kong
and Guangdong Province was formally signed today.
</P>
<P>
The agreement sets out a clear boundary of administration for
all sectors: the land boundary between the northern "New
Territories" and Shenzhen, the boundary in Deep Bay and Mirs Bay,
and the sea boundary to the west, south and east of Hong Kong,
according to the Government Information Services.
</P>
<P>
It is the product of 14 rounds of talks between Hong Kong and
Guangdong which began in 1988. Agreement on the boundary of
administration was reached in the 13th round of meeting in January
and the same boundary was formally signed today by Deputy
Political Adviser, John Ashton, on behalf of the Hong Kong
Government, and Xiao Jinzhe, deputy director of the Foreign
Affairs Office of the Guangdong Provincial Government.
</P>
<P>
"The boundary between Hong and Guangdong is one of the busiest
in the world. Millions of people cross it every month, as do large
numbers of cars, lorries, ships and boats, carrying a formidable
and growing amount of cross-border trade," said John Ashton.
</P>
</TEXT>
