<HEADLINE> U.S. Warplanes Leave Qatar for Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, June 19 (Xinhua)-- Thirty warplanes and over 1,000
airmen of U.S. air forces began to leave Qatar for home today
after completing their task of supporting U.N. sanctions over
Iraq, the Qatari news agency said.
</P>
<P>
The warplanes and airmen are from the fourth wing of the
U.S. Air Expeditionary Force (AEF) and were deployed in Qatar in
February.
</P>
<P>
The deployment is the second one for the U.S. armed forces in
Qatar. The first took place during the period from June 18 to
August 20 in 1996 when 34 U.S. fighter and tanker aircraft were
sent there.
</P>
<P>
The deployments came in the framework of a U.S-Qatar defense
agreement signed in 1992 after Iraq's invasion over Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. AEF is a light and lean package of aircraft and personnel
designed to deploy to a forward location and immediately employ
combat assets. 
</P>
