<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Election Monitoring Group Set up in Liberia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations (UN) and the
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) on Wednesday
set up a joint group in Monrovia to monitor the July 19 election
in Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Reports reaching here said the group was jointly chaired by
the Nigerian ambassador in Monrovia, Joshua Iroha, and the
special representative of the UN Secretary-General, Tuliameni
Kalomah.
</P>
<P>
The group will be responsible for ensuring that the
operational requirements of the electoral process are provided
and that the election will be free and fair.
</P>
<P>
For the success of the election, the international society has
promised to contribute a total of 15 million U.S. dollars as
financial support.
</P>
<P>
ECOWAS has also agreed to provide 1.5 million dollars, with
each of its 16 members contributing 100,000 dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
