<DOCNO> XIE19970619.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Fighting Drug Trafficking In Southeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- China's Fujian Province arrested
569 suspected drug traffickers and confiscated more than 320 kilos
of drugs in the first five months of the year.
</P>
<P>
Local police say that Fujian has also destroyed three drug
manufacturers and some plants used for making drugs since the
beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
The coastal province dealt with 410 cases of drug trafficking,
122 more than for the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
While it is cracking down on drug traffickers, the province is
also trying to help drug addicts by registering them and helping
them kick their habits. 
</P>
</TEXT>
