<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unknown Disease Kills 1,000 Cattle in Zambia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An unknown disease broke
out recently in Kalomo, southern Zambia, killing over 1,000 heads
of cattle and threatening 10,000 others.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail today quoted Dundumwezi Constituency
Chairman James Sibajane as saying on Wednesday that the
mysterious disease with unknown symptoms is on the rise and
threatens to wipe out the animal population in the district and
hence impoverishing the villagers who depend on the animals for the
livelihood.
</P>
<P>
Despite reports to the Agricultural Department in the
district, no constructive response has been made. But the
department defended itself saying it has no transport to
travel to the area to get the situation under control, said the
paper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
