</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- After two years of negotiations, the European Union (EU)
Intergovernmental Conference ended at early hours on Wednesday in a
severe failure for its 15 member countries. Although the new treaty
was a big improvement of the 1992 Maastricht treaty with new clauses
on interior security and the power of the European Parliament, the
EU leaders failed to agree upon the key issue of reforming EU
institutions and the decision-making process.
</P>
<P>
-- U.S. President Bill Clinton announced on Wednesday a great
``African initiative'' by America to build an American-African
partnership of growth which is aimed at helping the black continent
emerge as a ``stable, prosperous and democratic Africa.''  Termed
``a turning for Africa,'' the plan is described as a radical change
of the policy of the United States toward Africa.
</P>
