</P>
<P>
-- Prime Minister Lionel Jospin will speak to the parliament
today on the general policy of his government. Apart from calling
for a raise of the guaranteed minimum salary and the organization of
a job conference in September, Jospin is expected to refrain from
announcing any big decision concerning public budget spending.
</P>
<P>
The government spokeswoman Catherine Trautmann said that the
government would not propose a budget bill until September to
replace the 1997 budget law elaborated by the former government of
Prime Minister Alain Juppe.
</P>
<P>
-- French police have arrested 630 people since Tuesday in a
nationwide crackdown on a pedophile criminal network which produces
pornographic cassettes and corrupt the minors. 
