<HEADLINE> Iran Rejects U.S. Defense Secretary's Hostile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- An Iranian spokesman attacked
U.S. Defense Secretary William Cohen for his "poisonous
propaganda" against Iran with an aim to "create anxiety in the
region."
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Mohammadi, spokesman for the Iranian Foreign Ministry,
noted that the increased presence of foreign forces in the
Persian Gulf and the unchecked sales of weapons to the region are
the main obstacles on the way of establishment of security.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman, quoted by the official news agency IRNA today,
was making comments on Cohen's recent Gulf tour, during which the
U.S. official told Arab leaders that Iran is a threat to the
regional security.
</P>
<P>
Mohammadi added that Iran places a great importance on the
security of the Persian Gulf and considers security and
cooperation among the countries in the Persian Gulf region as a
must to this end.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, today's English daily Iran News published an
editorial entitled "Regional countries should not allow Cohen to
cast shadow on new trends in ties."
</P>
<P>
The daily noted that the U.S. defense secretary has adopted
"bullying tactics" against Iran to create the impression in the
sheikhdoms that there is a definite risk of another war in the
Persian Gulf.
</P>
<P>
The editorial urged the regional countries to be wise enough
not to allow Cohen to cast a shadow on the newly-fashioned trend
in regional relations.
</P>
<P>
"Iran has never adopted an aggressive posture toward its
neighbors in the southern Persian Gulf, and (President-elect
Mohammad) Khatami's election has helped allay most of the
imaginary fears of the region rulers regarding Tehran's future
policies," it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
