<HEADLINE> North China Develops Aquatic Product Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin municipal government
has worked to transform saline-alkali land into fish-raising
ponds. About 6,700 hectares of saline-alkali land in Tianjin will
be turned into fish-raising ponds.
</P>
<P>
The municipality has already spent 60 million yuan in building
3,333 hectares of fish-raising ponds, and raised dozens of quality
aquatic products as river crabs and a variety of fishes, with an
output of more than 20,000 tons and an income increase of 15
million yuan for peasants in 1996. 
</P>
