<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Rises in Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Israel
rose to 7.3 percent in the first quarter of this year, with some
160,000 people out of work, or a 12.3 percent increase from the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
According to the Central Bureau of Statistics, the unemployment
rate has risen from an average rate of 6.3 percent in the first
three quarters last year to 7.1 percent in the fourth quarter and
now 7.3 percent, the highest figure since the beginning of 1995.
</P>
<P>
Minister of Labor and Social Affairs Eli Ishai has called for
urgent measures to check high unemployment, particularly in the
remote developing towns.
</P>
<P>
Overall unemployment among men reached 6.4 percent, an
increase from 5.7 percent in the same period last year. Meanwhile,
there was 8.0 percent unemployment in the female population, 0.9
percentage point up from 7.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
The total civilian workforce numbered 2.17 million in the
first quarter, when the country's population reached 5.75 million,
a 2.6 percent increase on the equivalent 1996 figure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
