<HEADLINE> Thai Deputy PM Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Thai Deputy Prime Minister and
Finance Minister Amnuay Virawan resigned from his posts here
today, the Thai Government House officials confirmed.
</P>
<P>
Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh formally accepted
Amnuay's resignation this morning.
</P>
<P>
Thai Commerce Minister Narongchai Akrasanee, another key member
of Chavalit's economic "dream team", also resigned with Amnuay.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Industrial Minister Somphob Armartayakul is expected to
send a letter of resignation later as he is on trip abroad. Amnuay
Wednesday presented Chavalit a letter stating his intention to
resign, but did not give any reason.
</P>
<P>
Amnuay, Narongchai and Somphob are non-party members of the
cabinet who were appointed to the cabinet under the New Aspiration
Party's quota after Chavalit won the general election in November
last year to form the economic "dream team" to handle the
country's already troubled economy.
</P>
<P>
Local media said that the current economic woes in Thailand and
conflicts on economic affairs with the Chat Chattana Party, one of
the six ruling parties in the Chavalit coalition, were likely to
be among reasons behind Amnuay's resignation.  
</P>
</TEXT>
