<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 08:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rafsanjani Receives Message from Syrian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Akbar Hashemi
Rafsanjani has received a message from his Syrian counterpart
Hafez al-Assad, denouncing U.S.-Israeli moves to destabilize the
Middle East region.
</P>
<P>
The message was conveyed by Syrian Vice-President Abdul-Halim
Khaddam who paid a one-day visit here Wednesday, Iran's official
news agency IRNA reported today.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani and the Syrian vice-president held talks on their
stances toward the latest development in the region.
</P>
<P>
On the incursion of Turkish troops into northern Iraq and
Ankara's military cooperation with Israel, Khaddam said that "by
trying to create tension among Israel's neighboring countries,
Israel and the United States are preparing ground for their
intervention and illegitimate presence in the region."
</P>
<P>
He termed as another U.S.-Israeli plot the recent vote of the
U.S. House of Representatives to move the U.S. embassy from Tel
Aviv to Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam said that Syria is ready to hold frequent and top-level
consultations with Iran and other frontline states opposed to
Israel in order to pursue a coordinated common policy against such
a plot.
</P>
<P>
He said that al-Assad will participate in the summit of
heads of state of the Organization of the Islamic Conference
(OIC) to be held in Tehran in December 1997.
</P>
<P>
Referring to bilateral relations, the Syrian vice-president
said that Iran and Syria enjoy good relations due to historical
and religious commonalities, and the ties are growing day by day.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the bilateral relations should be further
deepened in order to prevent what he called the expansionist and
domineering alien powers from exercising control over the region.
</P>
<P>
Rafsanjani was quoted by the IRNA as saying that Iran fully
supports Muslim countries to oppose the sinister greed of alien
powers. He said that the United States and Israel are trying to
sow the seeds of discord by creating crises in the region in order
to justify their presence and domination there.
</P>
<P>
Condemning the U.S. Congress' resolution to recognize
Jerusalem as the undivided capital of Israel, Rafsanjani termed
it as a proof of Washington's disregard for the rights of millions
of Palestinian refugees and the demands of the Muslim world.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. has clearly demonstrated that its claim of being
impartial in the Arab-Israeli negotiations is but an empty one,
Rafsanjani noted.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president also expressed his concern over the
developments in northern Iraq, saying that Iran, Syria and all
other Islamic countries should take the responsibility to resolve
the crises in the region.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam left here for home Wednesday at the end of his official
visit and was seen off at the airport by his Iranian counterpart
Hassan Habibi. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
