<HEADLINE> National Roads Agency Set Up in S.Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The establishment of the South
African National Roads Agency (SANRA), an independent agency to handle
the country's road building and maintenance, has been approved by the
cabinet.
</P>
<P>
In terms of the South African National Roads Agency Bill endorsed
by the cabinet on Wednesday, road users will contribute more directly
through the petrol levy and toll fees for the building and maintenance
of roads in future, according to local press reports today.
</P>
<P>
Transport Minister Mac Maharaj said at the cabinet meeting
that the proposal to establish a dedicated roads agency has been
put forward after extensive studies on home and foreign
experiences.
</P>
<P>
"For the first time, road building and maintenance in South Africa
will be placed on a commercial footing," he said.
</P>
<P>
Thus sets up the need for the management of road as a national
resource, to be carried out with efficiency, accountability and
transparency, the minister added.
</P>
<P>
"The national roads, which are the key to economic growth in
South Africa, have been deteriorating due to decreasing funding,"
Maharaj noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
