<HEADLINE> Over 200 Rebels Killed in Western Ugandan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Over 200 rebels of the Allied
Democratic Forces (ADF) have been killed since Monday in fights
in the Bundibugyo District of western Uganda, "The New Vision"
reported today.
</P>
<P>
ADF raided the district town Monday and was later repulsed by
government troops.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday afternoon, government forces won the battle for
Ntandi some 14 kilometers north-east of Bundibugyo, where the
rebels set up their command post.
</P>
<P>
The overall casualties of government troops are not yet
available. But local media said John Rugumayo, assistant resident
councillor at Bundibugyo district, and Karujumbawho, an army
intelligence officer, are among the victims.
</P>
<P>
ADF is a rebel group operating in western Uganda. An early
official estimate put its number on 400-500.
</P>
<P>
The high command of Uganda Armed Forces headed by President
Yoweri Museveni will have a meeting today, discussing mainly
issues concerning ADF activities in Bundibugyo, an army source
said.
</P>
<P>
ADF rebels killed eight civilians in separate ambushes on
Wednesday and Tuesday in western part of the country, local media
reported today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
