<HEADLINE> China's Largest Sugar-Refining Company Group Established </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANNING, June 19 (Xinhua) -- China's largest sugar-refining
company group has been established in Nanning, capital of south
China's Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region.
</P>
<P>
Nanning Unified Sugar-Refining Co. Ltd, which was recently
listed as one of the 300 large enterprises that will be given
major support from the state, was formed by six state-owned
sugar-making enterprises in the city, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
The company group has a registered capital of 499 million yuan
and 708 million yuan of fixed assets. It will mainly engage in
businesses such as sugar refining, production of sugar-refining
machines, and comprehensive development of sugar refining.
</P>
<P>
The conglomerate is able to press 2.02 million tons of
sugarcane and produce 230,000 tons of cane sugar annually, with
the cane sugar output accounting for 10 percent of the regional
total.
</P>
<P>
The company group generated 948 million yuan of industrial
output value and created 107 million yuan of pre-tax profits in
1996. 
</P>
