<HEADLINE> Zhuhai Offers Wider Areas for Investment from Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Years of construction
have made Zhuhai, one of China's first special economic zones,
an investment spot popular among businesspeople from Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai will take full advantage of the return of Hong
Kong, China's international financial center, to attract more
capital from around the globe, says Zhong Jinlai, director of the
Municipal Commission for Foreign Trade and Economic Relations.
</P>
<P>
Completion of a large number of infrastructure facilities in
the city, including the airport, deep-water port and highway
networks, together with flexible policies and measures granted by
the government, has provided Zhuhai with a wider range of
investment options for Hong Kong, according to Zhong.
</P>
<P>
Zhuhai now boasts six functional districts, such as the free
trade zone, an aviation industrial town, and a high-tech
development zone.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's investment in Zhuhai has grown rapidly over the
past few years. Industries that produce computer discs and
software, auto parts and textiles have achieved advanced
production levels.
</P>
<P>
By the end of last year, Zhuhai had drawn 1.57 billion US
dollars of investment from Hong Kong, over half of all capital
absorbed from other countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
The completion of major bridges and passages to connect Zhuhai
and Hong Kong will further accelerate the economic cooperation
between the two zones, says Zhong. 
</P>
</TEXT>
