<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan's Environment Remains Sound </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The quality of the environment in
South China's Hainan Province remains sound, with the discharge of
waste gas, waste water and waste solids per unit GDP being lower
than the national average, despite its higher-than-average
economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The water quality of major waterways including Songtao and
Niulouling meets the first and second class standards set by the
state, better than the national average.
</P>
<P>
The province has some 1.7 million hectares of forests, with
forest cover at 50.2 percent. They include 866,000 hectares of
tropical virgin forests that help maintain the ecological
balance.
</P>
<P>
Hainan has also 73 natural reserves, covering an area of around
2.7 million hectares, ranking third in the country.
</P>
<P>
This largest special economic zone in China has made more than
20 laws and regulations concerning environment and resource
protection since it became a province in 1988.
</P>
<P>
Last year, the province closed down 75 heavily polluting
factories and ordered 583 others to improve pollution control
within a prescribed time limit.
</P>
<P>
The province strives to maintain its leading position in
environmental quality by the year 2000 by adopting high technology
and strict environmental protection standards for new industrial
projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970619.0233 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Shandong State Enterprises Produce Name Brand Products </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, June 19 (Xinhua) -- State-owned enterprises in east
China's Shandong Province are producing 90 percent of the
provincial name-brand products, promoting local economic growth.
</P>
<P>
The province has named 94 local products as Shandong name
brands, which rank among the first three in the national sectors,
or first in the province. Of the country's 19 well-known
registered trade marks, Shandong has contributed five.
</P>
<P>
Industry insiders attribute the good performance of state
enterprises to their improved reforms for labor, personnel and
distribution systems, under which employees compete for posts and
earn by contributions.
</P>
<P>
The province las selected 120 key enterprises to enjoy special
assistance from banks, and carried out 100 technological
improvement projects annually, in a move to cultivate pillar
industries and name brands. As a result, half its industrial
products sell elsewhere.
</P>
<P>
The Qingdao Haier Group Co. has bought into six otherwise
bankrupt businesses, and had 6.1 billion yuan in sales and 300
million yuan in profit last year. Its Haier Brand series of
electrical appliances are well-known nationwide as the country's
name-brand products.
</P>
<P>
Shandong mass-produces more than 2,000 major scientific and
technological research achievements annually, and 60 percent of
its industrial production growth came from them last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
