<HEADLINE> East China's Fujian to Improve Shipbuilding Industry </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- East China's Fujian Province will
put 2.3 billion yuan into its shipbuilding industry through the
year 2010 for technical improvements, according to local sources.
</P>
<P>
This will include building a 20,000-dwt (dead weight ton) berth
at Mawei, another 35,000-dwt berth and a 75,000-dwt dry dock in
Xiamen, and using new techniques in production,
</P>
<P>
The coastal province hopes that its shipbuilding industry will
generate four billion yuan in total output value by the year
2000. A 35,000-dwt ship repair center and an export base for
35,000-dwt container ships and large tugboats will be completed by
the year 2010.
</P>
<P>
Fujian has one of China's highly developed shipbuilding
industries. It has 108 shipbuilders and related support factories.
</P>
<P>
Mawei Shipyard is China's oldest, having been established in
1866. It has also decided to put 150 million yuan into large-scale
technical upgrading to reach its goal of producing five 10,000-dwt
container ships a year. 
</P>
