<HEADLINE> Regulations Ensure Enough Schools and Kindergartens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Changsha, the capital of Hunan
Province in Central China, has recently promulgated regulations on
the planning and construction of middle and primary schools and
kindergartens to ensure that there are enough schools and
kindergartens in new residential quarters.
</P>
<P>
The move is taken to check the tendency of occupying land
designated for schools and altering plans for building schools and
kindergartens in the city.
</P>
<P>
The regulations provide that all city district and counties
should incorporate the building of schools and kindergartens into
their economic and social development plans, making it in keeping
with the development of education.
</P>
<P>
Educational departments should be consulted when building and
planning schools and kindergartens. The land designated for
building such schools and kindergartens should be protected by law
and is not allowed to be used for other purposes.
</P>
<P>
The regulations also provide that there must be a primary
school and a kindergarten for a residential quarter with 4,000
families and there must be a middle school for a residential
quarter with 8,000 families. 
</P>
</TEXT>
