<HEADLINE> Bolivia Maintain Perfect Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MONTEVIDEO, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Copa America hosts Bolivia beat
Uruguay 1-0 Wednesday to complete their group matches with maximum
points and without conceding a goal.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia finished top of group B to join second-placed Peru, who
earlier beat Venezuela 2-0, in the quarter-finals. Defending
champions Uruguay were third with three points and will have to
wait until Thursday's final group C matches to know if they go
through as one of the two best of the three third-placed teams.
</P>
<P>
The result also qualified Paraguay, who finished third in group
A with four points, one more than Uruguay.
</P>
<P>
Julio Cesar Baldivieso scored the only goal in the 30th minute
when the Uruguayan defence left him unmarked at a corner, giving
him time to trap the ball on his chest, dribble past goalkeeper
and fire the ball into the empty net.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia will meet the second best third-placed team in their
semi-final in La Paz on Saturday while Peru face Argentina, who
finished second in group A, in Sucre the same day.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia's win averted a crisis which could have hit the
competition if they had finished second in the group.
</P>
<P>
Argentina threatened to pull out over an alteration in the
rules made on Tuesday when the Copa America organisers announced
that if Bolivia finished second, their quarter-final against the
second-placed group A team -- which turned out to be Argentina --
would be moved to La Paz, which stands 3,600 meters high above sea
level. 
</P>
</TEXT>
