Nationalist Party (BNP) has threatened to launch a countrywide
oust-government campaign next week if the administration does not
withdraw some proposals in the proposed budget for 1997-98 fiscal
year.
</P>
<P>
The BNP denounced as "anti-people" the proposed budget
presented to parliament a week ago, and demanded withdrawal of the
hiked price of fertiliser, news taxes and surcharge from the
budget to be put into effect on July 1.
</P>
<P>
As part of a "warm-up" program, the opposition will stage
protest rallies and demonstrations in all district headquarters
and all counties in the capital Dhaka tomorrow.
</P>
<P>
