headquarters and wards in Dhaka on Sunday and would announce a
countrywide "greater action program" to oust the government.
</P>
<P>
"The new budget is designed to kill the people. There will be
no way to live in the country if the budget is adopted, so there
is no alternative to a mass movement against the government," BNP
General Secretary Mannan Bhuiyan told a public meeting on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said Bangladesh would turn into a market of India completely
if the budget is passed. He demanded the government immediately
jettison its budget or face a tougher campaign.  
