<HEADLINE> East China City Controlling Ceramics Pollution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Quanzhou in Fujian province has
inspected several thousand ceramics factories in a move to check
pollution.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the Quanzhou city government began efforts to curb
ceramics pollution, stopping new ceramic projects which would
cause severe pollution and introducing advanced technology for old
factories.
</P>
<P>
About 2,000 chimneys in the four counties have been demolished,
and dust and smoke pollution has been put under control.
</P>
<P>
The environment protection department in Quanzhou has enhanced
efforts in this regard, penalizing ceramic factories that do not
follow regulations.
</P>
<P>
Many ceramic factories in the counties of Cizhao, Leikeng,
Guanqiao, and Shuitou along the Fuzhou-Xiamen highway had been
found to cause severe pollution, and they were asked to take
control measures.  
</P>
