<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- The Asia-Europe Business
Conference (AEBC) scheduled to be held in Jakarta, capital of
Indonesia, on July 8 to 10, will be attended by about 400
participants from 15 European Union countries and 10 Asian
countries, an official said here today.
</P>
<P>
AEBC Organizing Committee Chairman Soy M. Pardede said that
Asia will be represented by China, Japan, South Korea, as well as
member countries of the ASEAN, namely Brunei, Indonesia, Malaysia,
the Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The AEBC is a follow-up to the Asia-Europe Business Forum held
in Paris in October last year when the agreement was reached that
Asian and European businessmen meet here in July.
</P>
<P>
The Asia-Europe Business Forum itself was held following a
decision taken in the Asia-Europe Meeting (ASEM) held in Bangkok
in March 1996.
</P>
<P>
Pardede said the AEBC is aimed at establishing business contact
to promote the spirit of partnership between Asian and European
business circles.
</P>
<P>
