<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Gem Industry Loses Billions </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, June 19 (Xinhua)-- Sri Lanka's gem industry has lost
billions of rupees of potential earnings from Geuda (a kind of
gem) during the past five years due to lack of expertise.
</P>
<P>
According to the Director General of the National Gem and
Jewelry Authority (NGJA) P.G.R. Dharmaratne, these earnings
represent 37 million carats of Geuda taken to Thailand for 43.1
million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
He said this money could have been earned by Sri Lanka if Sri
Lankans had been trained in Geuda Treatment Technology and
popularized it widely.
</P>
<P>
Thai buyers have purchased 8.6 million US dollars worth of
Geudas from Sri Lanka in 1996 and increased their value by 100
percent by using heat treatment technology.
</P>
<P>
20,000 persons employed in Thailand were mainly dependent on
the Sri Lankan Geuda, according to the Director.
</P>
<P>
He said if the gem industry is significantly developed in Sri
Lanka it would generate a significant amount of foreign exchange
for the country while Sri Lanka's unemployment problem can be
reduced to a great extent by improving the gem industry. 
</P>
</TEXT>
