<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Investment Backing Central China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong investors have been
playing an important role in the social and economic growth of
Zhengzhou, the capital of central China's Henan Province, with 400
million US dollars in investment already spent.
</P>
<P>
Zhengzhou is a land-locked city with sustained economic growth
in recent years thanks to Hong Kong investment, which is nearly
half the city's total, focusing on electronics, food, light
industries, and real estate.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong businessmen have had 1,036 projects in the city in
the past few years, and most joint ventures funded by Hong Kong
businessmen are showing profits, with residential construction
having been brisk in recent years.
</P>
<P>
An electronics joint venture, "Huawei", exported 16 million US
dollars worth of products last year, raking first among local
foreign-funded enterprises. And Hongrun Textile Co., Ltd, jointly
built by a local state-owned textile enterprise and Hong Kong
investors, exported about 90 percent of its products last year.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong investors provided about half of the investment in
real estate development in Zhengzhou, and are very active in local
service industries, a Chinese official says  
</P>
</TEXT>
