<HEADLINE> World Bank Approves Loans for Indonesian Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The World Bank today announced
the approval of two loans totaling 87.6 million U.S. dollars for
Indonesia's education and government audit modernization projects.
</P>
<P>
The first loan of 71.2 million dollars is earmarked for the
country's undergraduate education project aimed at helping to
improve the quality of undergraduate study programs of national
priority, such as engineering and technology, health, agriculture
and basic science.
</P>
<P>
The total project cost is estimated at 109.06 million
dollars. Apart from the World Bank loan, the remaining 37.9
million dollars will come from the government of Indonesia and the
beneficiary study program through the universities' self-generated
revenue.
</P>
<P>
Another loan of 16.4 million dollars is provided as technical
assistance for Indonesia's BEPEKA Audit Modernization Project
designed to strengthen the capacity of the country's highest
auditing agency, the State Audit Board (BEPEKA).
</P>
<P>
The estimated total project cost of 26.6 million dollars will
also be shared by the Indonesian government contribution of 10.1
million dollars in addition to the World Bank loan. 
</P>
</TEXT>
