<HEADLINE> World Metropolitan Mayors Conference Opens in Moscow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The Fifth Conference of World
Metropolitan Mayors opened here today and is focusing on
metropolitan ecology, anti-crime activities, supply and
transportation.
</P>
<P>
Russian President Boris Yeltsin told the conference in a
telegram that it is important for proper predictions and future
proposals to analyze the developing trend of metropolises in the
next millennium. They were the centers of national politics,
economies and cultures.
</P>
<P>
Mayor of Moscow City Yuri Luzhkov suggested that criteria for
the life to be formed in metropolises be created through the
mixtures of cultures and ideas.
</P>
<P>
Greeting the three-day conference, United Nations
Secretary-General Kofi Annan said he hoped it would help solve the
global problems of unemployment, high crime rates, environmental
pollution and lack of homes.
</P>
<P>
The Conference of World Metropolitan Mayors is held every three
years. The first was in Tokyo in 1985.
</P>
<P>
Moscow, celebrating the 850th anniversary of its founding,
gained the right to host this conference after defeating Mexico
City and Vienna. 
</P>
</TEXT>
