<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beilun Port Now No. 3 In China In Cargo-Handling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Ningbo City's Beilun Port, in
Zhejiang Province, handled 76 million tons of goods, making it
third in China and one of the best in the country due to its
deep-water docks.
</P>
<P>
Beilun has 22 docks, which can accommodate 10,000-DWT vessels,
including one designed to handle 200,000-DWT mineral vessels and a
dock that can handle 250,000-DWT oil tankers.
</P>
<P>
The port has been designed for cooperation with neighboring big
harbors, mainly Shanghai. And, iron ore imports from Brazil,
Australia, and South Africa have been shipped to Beilun by
international carriers and then trans-shipped to industrial cities
along the Yangtze River, lowering transport cost.
</P>
<P>
To do all this, the port authorities have spent on
technological renovations to keep up with the rest of the world.
</P>
<P>
The port can now handle the latest model containers, with an
annual capacity of 800,000 TEU. By the end of the century, the
capacity is expected to top 100 million TEU. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
