<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Thailand's Sugar Cane Output to Drop in Next Season </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Thailand's sugar cane yield for
the current season totaled 56 million tons, according to a Thai
Industry Ministry source.
</P>
<P>
However, the source warned that the cane production is likely
to fall by about 10 percent to 52 million tons for the 1997-98
season on last year's level of 57 million tons, for lack of
rainfall.
</P>
<P>
A Thai industry analyst predicted that world sugar prices would
briefly decline when supplies from Australia and Thailand, the
second and third sugar producers, came on the market in July and
December.
</P>
<P>
World sugar production this year is estimated to total 123.4
million tons, up by 2 percent on last year's, while consumption is
put at 122 million tons.
</P>
<P>
World sugar prices are currently promising and some analysts
believe that they could stay so next year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
