<HEADLINE> Cultural Activities in North China Province Popular </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, June 19 (Xinhua) -- More local people in the
capital of Hebei Province have a chance to take part in cultural
activities on weekends.
</P>
<P>
Many people here are fond of going to libraries, attending
concerts, or visiting museums during their two days off.
</P>
<P>
Xia Menghua, a librarian at the Hebei Library, says that a lot
of readers began to come here on the weekend since the beginning
of last year, and many workers and businessmen come to read after
a busy week.
</P>
<P>
Many residents also go to the 2,000-sq.m. book center in the
city, while exhibitions at the Hebei Museum, the largest in the
province, have attracted many people, especially middle school
students who are eager to learn more about culture and history.
</P>
<P>
