information about his government's policy on the property
confiscated in his country from U.S. citizens.
</P>
<P>
Before going to Washington, Aleman will attend a U.N. General
Assembly meeting in New York to make a speech on the environmental
problem next Monday.
</P>
<P>
In New York, the Nicaraguan president will meet his Argentine
counterpart Carlos Menem and U.N. Secretary-General Kofi Annan
"who is very interested in knowing about the democratic process in
Nicaragua and its economic development program."
</P>
<P>
President Aleman will return to Nicaragua on June 26. 
