<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesian Expert: World's Environment Worsened </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, June 19 (Xinhua) -- Five year after the 1992 earth
summit in Rio de Janeiro, conditions of the environment across the
globe have deteriorated, an Indonesian expert said.
</P>
<P>
Dr. Emil Salim, a former population and environment minister
and currently chairman of a private organization dedicated to
bio-diversity, said here Wednesday that in the years since the Rio
de Janeiro summit, the world progressed in economic but not in
environmental terms.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a discussion to welcome a special United Nations
session in New York next June 23-27 to review implementation of
the earth summit's agenda-21, Salim said the volume of green house
emissions which cause global warming was increasing and so were
the global rates of gas, solid and liquid wastes.
</P>
<P>
Sources at the discussion today quoted Salim as saying that
rivers and seas were increasingly becoming polluted, stocks of
fish were declining and bio-diversity was undergoing heavy
pressure.
</P>
<P>
Of late, global warming and the impacts of climate changes were
increasingly felt as reflected in seasonal changes in the
agricultural production patterns and production failures.
</P>
<P>
Salim also mentioned the relationship between environmental
degradation on a global scale and the emergence of new diseases
such as AIDS and other infectious illnesses.
</P>
<P>
He said new environment-friendly methods to exploit natural
resources must be devised.
</P>
<P>
Salim hoped the special U.N. meeting to evaluate the results of
the earth summit, would help renew and strengthen the commitments
made by the world's countries five years ago. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
