<HEADLINE> 49 Arrested in Drugs Sweep </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Rome, June 18 (Xinhua) -- 49 drug traffickers from an organized
crime ring supplying Italian market with cocaine, custasy and
hashish from Equador, England, France, Spain and the Netherlands
was smashed today by police.
</P>
<P>
Working under the command of the police in Vicenza, a
northeastern city in Italy, the arrests were carried out in 12
Italian cities from Trieste to Milan and from Turin to Rome by 300
policemen, backed by helicopters and dogs.
</P>
<P>
Police said investigators on the case since June last year
brought to light trafficking in which 200 kilograms of cocaine,
2,000 of hashish and 80,000 ecstasy pills were tracked through the
network.
</P>
<P>
Ahead of today's operation, police seized a total of 698
kilograms of hashish, 6,000 ecstasy pills and 600 grams of
cocaine. 
