<HEADLINE> Schuster Moves into Coaching with Cologne Job </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Former German international Bernd
Schuster began a career as a coach on Wednesday when he took
charge of second division side Fortuna Cologne.
</P>
<P>
The former Barcelona midfielder, who has been involved in
controversy at almost all his previous clubs, left Mexican side
UNAM in April and has been back in Germany studying for a coaching
qualification.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, who won 21 caps for West Germany before quitting the
national side over a dispute with his team-mates, said Fortuna had
approached him at the weekend.
</P>
<P>
Schuster, nicknamed the "blond angel" by the German press,
played for Atletico and Real Madrid as well as Barcelona during
his spell in Spain.
</P>
<P>
He last played in Germany for Bayer Leverkusen but left under a
cloud last year, gaining a huge compensation payout from the club
which had banned him from playing during a legal dispute between
him and senior officials. 
</P>
</TEXT>
