<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roberto Carlos Signs New Contract with Real </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Real Madrid have reached terms with
Roberto Carlos which will keep the set-piece specialist at the
Spanish league champions until 2002, the club announced on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Under the contract, any club wanting to buy the Brazilian
international will have to pay $100 million, the highest
withdrawal clause in the history of the Spanish game.
</P>
<P>
Roberto Carlos' salary has not been disclosed, and he has
not yet signed the contract as he is in Bolivia with Brazil at
the Copa America tournament. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
