<DATE_TIME> 1997-06-19 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Black Sea Parliamentary Assembly Meeting Begins in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, June 18 (Xinhua) -- The 9th Plenary Session of the
Black Sea Economic Cooperation's Parliamentary Assembly (PABSEC)
opened here today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking in his opening speech, Greek President Costis
Stephanopoulos stressed that the Black Sea had always been "a
vital crossroads between Asia and Europe" and "a meeting place" of
different cultures, religions and nationalities.
</P>
<P>
He said that the promotion of economic cooperation in the
greater area of the black sea was an element for the progress of
the countries in the region and for peace and security in a region
which had from time to time suffered from great tension.
</P>
<P>
The president said that the inauguration of the Black Sea
Economic Cooperation (BSEC) bank in the northern Greek port city
of Thessaloniki would usher in a new important period of
cooperation among the countries of the region.
</P>
<P>
Greece would continue its efforts with undiminished interest
because this cooperation indeed contributed considerably to the
construction of the new Europe, he said.
</P>
<P>
The parliamentary assembly today unanimously approved
Bulgaria's accession to the forum.
</P>
<P>
Parliamentary members from all ten member-states, Greece,
Albania, Armenia, Azerbaijan, Georgia, Moldova, Romania, Russia,
Turkey and Ukraine, are participating in the two-day meeting which
focuses on a number of economic, political and social issues.
</P>
<P>
The president of the Bulgarian parliament has also been invited
to attend the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Also attending as observers are representatives of Egypt,
Israel and the U.N. High Commission for Refugees.
</P>
<P>
PABSEC, created in 1993, is the parliamentary wing of the Black
Sea Economic Cooperation organization, which aims to facilitate
cooperation among Black Sea countries and turn the region into a
zone of stability, prosperity and peace.
</P>
<P>
Currently, Greece is holding the rotating presidency of PABSEC.
</P>
</TEXT>
