<BODY>
<HEADLINE> European Shares End Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, June 18 (Xinhua) -- Shares on Europe's major stock
markets ended lower today.
</P>
<P>
Britain's FTSE-100 share index weakened for the third straight
session. The leading share index closed 25.2 points lower at
4,657. It has dropped 125 points this week since reaching a record
closing high on last Friday.
</P>
<P>
In Frankfurt, the DAX-30 index of leading German shares
finished at 3,730.27, down 11.21 points.
</P>
<P>
French shares closed weaker after a day of relatively light
trading amid investor caution ahead of Socialist Prime Minister
Lionel Jospin's debut parliamentary policy speech on Thursday. The
CAC-40 index ended at 2,751.74, down 10.86 points. 
</P>
</TEXT>
